things like that on paper.

00:37:13.060 --> 00:37:15.750
And if you've seen 3D
renderings of molecules

00:37:15.750 --> 00:37:19.620
or plastic 3D models of
molecules, those are lies, too.

00:37:19.620 --> 00:37:20.980
Because-- I mean they're closer.

00:37:20.980 --> 00:37:22.620
Molecules are
three-dimensional things,

00:37:22.620 --> 00:37:25.420
but they aren't
rigid things at all.

00:37:25.420 --> 00:37:30.070
This is actually what
molecules really look like.

00:37:30.070 --> 00:37:33.480
They're, generally
speaking, very flexible,

00:37:33.480 --> 00:37:37.620
floppy things that are
in constant motion.

00:37:37.620 --> 00:37:39.120
They're always vibrating.

00:37:39.120 --> 00:37:40.910
And so what we have
in the "Molecules" app

00:37:40.910 --> 00:37:45.440
is this high-end piece of
molecular dynamic simulation

00:37:45.440 --> 00:37:48.390
software that's normally
a supercomputer thing,

00:37:48.390 --> 00:37:50.470
but we're doing it
with small molecules.

00:37:50.470 --> 00:37:53.550
And it's doing quantum
mechanics guided

00:37:53.550 --> 00:37:58.990
simulation, legitimate molecular
dynamic simulation of what

00:37:58.990 --> 00:38:00.670
