AUDIENCE: Over there.

00:43:07.895 --> 00:43:09.020
THEODORE GRAY: There we go.

00:43:09.020 --> 00:43:10.350
Perfect, OK.

00:43:10.350 --> 00:43:13.524
Oh, great.

00:43:13.524 --> 00:43:15.440
Yeah, so it turns out
that steel wool actually

00:43:15.440 --> 00:43:18.654
burns very nicely, and
it's quite attractive

00:43:18.654 --> 00:43:21.972
when it works right.

00:43:21.972 --> 00:43:25.200
I just light it
here, and then you

00:43:25.200 --> 00:43:30.730
get this lovely kind of little
worms of fire coming up.

00:43:30.730 --> 00:43:35.460
And you notice that it's
different from most kinds

00:43:35.460 --> 00:43:37.900
of fire that you see, because
the fire is happening right

00:43:37.900 --> 00:43:39.421
on the surface of the metal.

00:43:39.421 --> 00:43:41.920
Normally, when you have wood
burning or something like that,

00:43:41.920 --> 00:43:43.540
the fire is above the wood.

00:43:43.540 --> 00:43:45.373
And that's because
what's actually happening

00:43:45.373 --> 00:43:47.159
is that the wood
is volatilizing,

00:43:47.159 --> 00:43:48.950
and there's flammable
gases that are going.

00:43:48.950 --> 00:43:50.200
Well, it's the gas
above that's really

00:43:50.200 --> 00:43:51.400
doing most of the burning.

00:43:51.400 --> 00:43:53.150
But here, nothing
volatilizes, and there's

00:43:53.150 --> 00:43:56.720
no smoke, other than a tiny bit
from residual oil on the steel

00:43:56.720 --> 00:43:57.221
wool.

00:43:57.221 --> 00:43:58.720
Because what's
happening is the iron

00:43:58.720 --> 00:44:02.000
is being converted in
place into iron oxide.

00:44:02.000 --> 00:44:04.180
And, actually, what's
happening, this is rusting.

00:44:04.180 --> 00:44:07.600
This is just high-speed rust.

00:44:07.600 --> 00:44:09.430
And rusting is a very
exothermic process.

00:44:09.430 --> 00:44:12.630
And it when happens fast
enough, things get hot,

00:44:12.630 --> 00:44:15.350
and then we call it fire.

00:44:15.350 --> 00:44:18.490
But really, it's just rusting.

00:44:18.490 --> 00:44:20.990
And it puts itself out, because
there's not much left to do.

