00:45:12.400 --> 00:45:14.295
Another class of
compounds that's on there

00:45:14.295 --> 00:45:16.110
is chlorofluorocarbons.

00:45:16.110 --> 00:45:17.626
So that debate is
kind of over now.

00:45:17.626 --> 00:45:20.000
And actually, I was just
reading just after the book went

00:45:20.000 --> 00:45:21.830
to press that for
the first time,

00:45:21.830 --> 00:45:24.010
the ozone hole is
getting better again now.

00:45:24.010 --> 00:45:26.170
It's like there's actually
been some progress

00:45:26.170 --> 00:45:29.400
in atmospheric science.

00:45:29.400 --> 00:45:34.090
But there was a time when
there was tremendous discord

00:45:34.090 --> 00:45:36.970
about that and people
calling each other names.

00:45:39.480 --> 00:45:41.200
And one of the
arguments that was made

00:45:41.200 --> 00:45:44.060
is that chlorofluorocarbons,
particularly in aerosol cans,

00:45:44.060 --> 00:45:47.520
